The paper proposes a novel multi-task 3D convolutional neural network model for classification, segmentation, and structural recovery of macromolecules in subtomograms. This involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and machine learning (ML) techniques such as multi-task learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves ML techniques such as CNNs and multi-task learning, which are related to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with cryo-tomography, which is related to the category cs.MM (Multimedia).
